HEADWORD: eyecup
<hw>eye"cup`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small oval
porcelain or glass cup, having a rim curved to fit the orbit of the eye.
it is used in the application of liquid remedies to eyes; -- called also
<altname>eyeglass</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
